		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://popdigital.ca/?p=52</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[I would have thought that solutions to this scenario would have been all over Google, but alas I had to dig to find snippets of information that eventually allowed me to write the code that I wanted. What I wanted: A list of my top 5 blog posts to appear on my WordPress site&#8217;s static [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I would have thought that solutions to this scenario would have been all over Google, but alas I had to dig to find snippets of information that eventually allowed me to write the code that I wanted.</p>
<p><strong>What I wanted:</strong> A list of my top 5 blog posts to appear on my WordPress site&#8217;s static homepage, with the blog&#8217;s title and a small amount of the blog&#8217;s text. I also wanted the &#8220;more&#8221; text to be a link to the actual blog post.</p>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
<p>1. Add the following to your theme&#8217;s functions.php file (inside the &lt;?php &#8230; ?&gt; tags):</p>
<pre>function home_excerpt_length($length) {
return 10; // The length of the excerpt text in characters
}

function home_excerpt_more($more) {
global $post;
return ' &lt;a href="'. get_permalink($post-&gt;ID) . '"&gt;[more...]&lt;/a&gt;';
}</pre>
<p>2. Add the following to your front-page.php file (or whatever template file you are using) at the spot on the page where you want the blog excerpts to appear:</p>
<pre>&lt;?php
query_posts('posts_per_page=5');
add_filter('excerpt_length', 'home_excerpt_length');
add_filter('excerpt_more', 'home_excerpt_more');
if (have_posts()) :
while (have_posts()) :
the_post();
echo "&lt;h3&gt;";
the_title();
echo "&lt;/h3&gt;";
the_excerpt();
endwhile;
endif;
?&gt;</pre>
]]></content:encoded>
